United Kingdom Secretary of State for Defence, Liam Fox announces plans to reduce the British Army to its smallest size since the start of the Second Boer War just over a century ago. By 2020, troop numbers will be reduced from the present 101,000 to 82,000, with a greater reliability on Territorial Army soldiers. (Sky News) (The Guardian)China tightens control of monasteries and on main roads in Tibet following deadly protests in the region. (Indian Express)